cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is about comparing two state-of-the-art policy optimization algorithms for robot control. The algorithms are evaluated on a continuous version of the mountain car benchmark problem, which is a classic control problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
